transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir. I was calling to get some information. I had had an order that I had placed.

Speaker 1: And in the – when you do the preliminary where you kind of get your information, they actually hadn't tried any other types.

Speaker 2: And so I had put what I had tried before. And so my order was supposed to be actual Viagra, period.

Speaker 1: And they sent me that sentence form.

Speaker 2: What was your first and last name?

Speaker 1: First name is Richard. Last name is Strzok.

Speaker 2: Okay, Mr. Strzok, I have your information up here. I see the prescription should have been written for our new Viagra AGV.

Speaker 1: And is that not what you got?

Speaker 2: That's not what I got. They sent me that Sildenafil or whatever they call it.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay. So the pill still will be technically named Sildenafil, but that doesn't mean that what you got is correct or incorrect.

Speaker 2: No, but it says generic on it for Viagra is what it says.

Speaker 1: So that's what the AGV stands for, Authorized Generic Viagra. It is – it's basically their generic version.

Speaker 2: They're from Pfizer. But what is – do you have those pills there in front of you?

Speaker 1: You could have still gotten the wrong thing.

Speaker 2: Let me grab them.

Speaker 1: Yeah, please.

Speaker 2: Let me grab them real quick.

Speaker 1: Sorry about that.

Speaker 2: Yeah, the important thing is the manufacturer, where it comes from, and I'll be able to tell that in just a second when you get the pills.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Sorry about that. If you did get the wrong thing, of course, I'll send you a replacement order. Absolutely.

Speaker 1: But let's just make sure.

Speaker 2: I'll send these back to you, whatever. All right. What would you need?

Speaker 1: What do the markings on the actual pills say, Mr. Strzok?

Speaker 2: Let me get one out.

Speaker 1: Let me see.

Speaker 2: All right. It says AC-340.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so that definitely is incorrect. You're right about that.

Speaker 2: So that is a generic pill. That's not the Viagra AGV that you should have gotten, Mr. Strzok.

Speaker 1: So I'm really sorry about that.

Speaker 2: Of course, like I said, I'm going to send you out a replacement order of these 10 pills stat.

Speaker 1: You'll see those come by before Friday for sure.

Speaker 2: I'm not going to charge you. Of course, you've already paid the pills that you have.

Speaker 1: You don't have to keep them. You can toss them.

Speaker 2: You don't have to send them back or anything like that because we're not going to resell them or anything.

Speaker 1: Those are still like American-made generic Viagra, just very similar to what the guys get from the VA.

Speaker 2: They're not the AGV.

Speaker 1: But I'm going to send you that new order right now.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Those are going to come by in the next few days.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry about that, Mr. Strzok.

Speaker 1: When this new order comes out, the markings on the pills will be different,

Speaker 2: and the label will indicate the AGV as well, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I mean, I'll send these back that way you normally get.

Speaker 1: I mean, I just got them today.

Speaker 2: Don't worry about that. That's our mistake, Mr. Strzok.

Speaker 1: You don't have to send that back.

Speaker 2: Keep them. You can save them for a rainy day.

Speaker 1: You can dispose of them.

Speaker 2: Don't worry about sending them back.

Speaker 1: Okay. Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: I just wanted to make sure because I thought they were the wrong stuff.

Speaker 2: I said, well, that's not really what I thought I was ordering.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you were correct about that.

Speaker 2: So that is a mix-up.

Speaker 1: I'm going to reach out to the pharmacy, and you won't see that happen again.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: You're all set then, Mr. Strzok.

Speaker 1: I'm really sorry about that.

Speaker 2: You'll see that come out in the next few days.

Speaker 1: My name is Leo, by the way.

Speaker 2: I'm the one who helped you out today.

Speaker 1: Okay. I appreciate it so much.

Speaker 2: So you think you'll be here, when do you think?

Speaker 1: I mean, I know Wednesday, Thursday.

Speaker 2: Wednesday. Okay.

Speaker 1: All right. All right.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Well, I appreciate your help so much.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: I'm so sorry about that.

Speaker 2: You'll enjoy the rest of your day, Mr. Strzok.

Speaker 1: All right. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye now.

Speaker 1: Okay.
